There is no perfect electric scooter in India. Middle class think of EV to save money and think of scooter as family vehicle which carry people and luggage (from grocery to gas cylinder)  

If premium brand like Ather sounds like rich people's toy, so called family scooter lacks on one or other qualities of traditional ICE scooter (TVS hub motor not suitable for uneven Indian roads, Bajaj hardly got language space). OLA pathetic build quality and non existent after sales service. May be as EV tech evolve further, we may get electric scooters Which can compete with ICE scooters.
